text:
Riverside Park: Grade crossing elimination on the New York Central tracks at W. 133rd Street. Shown, too is Riverside Drive viaduct.

October 16, 1925

East 133rd Street, at, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Park Ave., as seen thru clearance at the S.W. corner.

December 16, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

West 133rd Street, west from Park Ave. Clock tower shown, is on the James Everard Brewery, which is located on the south side of East 133rd Street, between Madison and Fifth Aves. The empty lot shown in the foreground, is at the S.W. corner of Park Ave.

December 16, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

Park Ave., west side, north from, and including East 133rd to 135th Street, showing the Central Coal Co. coal bins at the Harlem River. Also shown, is No. 1980, a 5-story tenement house (foreground), at the N.W. corner of East 133rd Street, and bearing No. 65 of the latter street.

December 16, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
